Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:23.46,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(298,0)}We sigh whenever we're about to come to a standstill
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:29.71,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}While moving on this endless journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.43,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Everytime we lunge for it, it escapes and flies off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:44.85,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}But now, there's nothing to be afraid of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:52.78,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}The powerful ties that bind our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:58.24,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Will never come loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:07.96,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9}After a lifetime of searching, we finally arrived
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.76,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Here, where the period lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:23.06,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}Let's change all our sorrow and rage to power.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.98,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,298}Destiny is right within our reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:23.46,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(298,0)}終わりなき旅の途中　立ち止まりそうな時
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:29.71,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}深いため息こぼす　僕らは
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.43,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}掴みかけてはまた離れていった
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:44.85,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}でも今はもう何も恐れることはない
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:52.78,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}心を繋ぐ強い絆は
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:58.24,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}けして解けはしないさ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:07.96,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9}探し続けて辿り着いた
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.76,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}この場所で {\fsp8}Perio{\fsp3.2}d に
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:23.06,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}悲しみ怒り 力に変えて
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.98,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,298}運命はすぐそばに
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:23.46,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(298,0)}Owarinaki tabi no tochuu tachidomarisouna toki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:29.71,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Fukai tameiki kobosu bokura wa
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.43,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Tsukamikaketewa mata hanareteitta
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:44.85,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Demo ima wa mou nanimo osoreru koto wa nai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:52.78,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}Kokoro wo tsunagu tsuyoi kizuna wa
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:58.24,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Keshite hodoke wa shinai sa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:07.96,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9}Sagashitsuzukete tadoritsuita
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.76,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Kono basho de piriodo ni
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:23.06,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}Kanashimi ikari chikara ni kaete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.98,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,298}Unmei wa sugu soba ni
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:22:00.21,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}The promise we never made
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.21,0:22:01.00,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}yet again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:05.84,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}tries to snatch our future away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:11.43,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that we can't rejoice
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.43,0:22:12.43,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}straight from the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:17.39,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}when we obtain something we've always been after?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.06,0:22:23.11,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,498}The overflowing tears aren't from feebleness or remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.77,0:22:27.90,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,258)}They're fragments born from agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.57,0:22:32.95,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Of all the moments and destinies,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.95,0:22:41.71,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}I realized there's one absolute certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.71,0:22:44.25,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if things get tough and I'm at my limit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.25,0:22:48.26,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:53.14,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:23:00.98,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}I can feel the warmth of your right hand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.98,0:23:04.65,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}where it's tightly joined with my left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:22:00.21,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}交わしたはずのない約束が
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.21,0:22:01.00,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}今日も
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:05.84,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}僕らの未来を奪おうとする
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:11.43,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,欲しがっていたものを手にしても
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.43,0:22:12.43,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}素直に
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:17.39,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}うまく笑えないのはなぜだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.06,0:22:23.11,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,498}あふれる涙は　弱さや後悔じゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.77,0:22:27.90,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,258)}イタミが生んだカケラで
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.57,0:22:32.95,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}どんな瞬間だって運命だって
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.95,0:22:41.71,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}ひとつだけ確かなものがあると知った
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.71,0:22:44.25,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,限界だって困難だって
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.25,0:22:48.26,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,あきらめたくないよ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:53.14,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,このまま離さないで
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:23:00.98,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}かたく握りしめた　君の右手のぬくもり
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.98,0:23:04.65,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}ここにあるから
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:22:00.21,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Kawashita hazu no nai yakasoku ga
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.21,0:22:01.00,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Kyou mo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:05.84,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}Bokura no mirai wo ubaou to suru
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:11.43,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshigatteita mono wo te ni shitemo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.43,0:22:12.43,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Sunao ni
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:17.39,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}Umaku waraenai nowa nazedarou
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.06,0:22:23.11,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,498}Afureru namida wo yowasa ya koukai ja nai
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.77,0:22:27.90,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,258)}Itami ga unda kakera de
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.57,0:22:32.95,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Donna shunkan datte unmei datte
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.95,0:22:41.71,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Hitotsu dake tashika na mono ga aru to shitta
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.71,0:22:44.25,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkai datte konnan datte
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.25,0:22:48.26,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Akirametakunaiyo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:53.14,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Konomama hanasanaide
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:23:00.98,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Kataku nigirishimeta kimi no migite no nukumori
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.98,0:23:04.65,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}Koko ni arukara
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.53,0:01:38.86,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,So you're suggesting Major General Armstrong had a hand in Lieutenant General Raven's disappearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.86,0:01:39.99,Default,Gel,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.99,0:01:43.58,Default,Gel,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure she left no evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.12,0:01:45.00,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.37,0:01:50.21,Default,Gel,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well. Our job is to take over this fort...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.21,0:01:55.30,Default,Gel,0000,0000,0000,,...while that fox is being investigated in Central by a herd of tigers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:05.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if it isn't the Major General.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:08.81,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't believe you were transferred to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.81,0:02:10.19,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What connections did you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:12.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it's simply an honest display of my capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:15.40,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Says the fresh meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.49,0:02:20.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What brings you here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.20,0:02:23.37,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I've been summoned by the Führer President.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.37,0:02:25.74,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I may not be able to return to Briggs for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.08,0:02:28.29,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,"For a while"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.71,0:02:31.50,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm going to have to take you to dinner at least once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:32.63,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Is it your treat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:36.17,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll let me eat until you go bankrupt, I don't mind going for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.59,0:02:38.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll give up on the meal, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.63,0:02:41.97,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Both your wallet and your balls are pea-sized, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.64,0:02:45.18,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,How about some flowers instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:50.10,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,There are many great florists in Central, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.85,0:02:51.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:02:58.15,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,You may enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.15,0:02:59.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.83,0:03:12.17,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Major General Armstrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:16.55,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,...let me hear more about\NLieutenant General Raven's disappearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:18.80,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.42,0:03:21.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to hide this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.43,0:03:28.81,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Why would a man as great as you choose to place a fool like Raven by his side?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.77,0:03:33.44,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,So you got rid of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.44,0:03:35.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:39.36,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Having a subordinate with such a loose tongue would do you no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.32,0:03:43.57,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,What did Lieutenant General Raven tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:45.45,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Something about an immortal army...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:48.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,...the history of this country, and your real identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:52.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,He told me many things I didn't even ask for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:03:59.09,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,So you still chose to respond to\Nmy summons after hearing all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:03.30,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to request the seat the idiot had been placing his ass on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.80,0:04:09.06,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting, as expected of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.35,0:04:13.69,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. You may have the position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:18.69,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange, I'll have one of my men govern over Briggs. Are you fine with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.23,0:04:20.90,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:24.45,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They are powerful soldiers I trained with great care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:27.07,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.78,0:04:32.83,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting. Do your best, human.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:40.67,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,"Nothing ventured, nothing gained."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:43.97,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,So the Major General ventured into the enemy's lair by her own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.38,0:04:47.47,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This place also belongs to them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:50.10,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,But they're unaware...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.47,0:04:59.94,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,...Briggs is a giant monolith that can act with a united will, even if its master happens to be away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:04.74,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,From here on, it's a war between bears and tigers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:14.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Is that seat free?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:17.67,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:22.25,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,How's your work progressing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:23.80,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:27.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I can't finish everything unless I multitask during my meals, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.80,0:05:29.80,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:33.56,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,There's so much to memorize; I'm fairly busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.10,0:05:37.19,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,But the Führer President does his job very quickly, so I do not have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:38.69,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't loaf either, unlike a certain someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.06,0:05:42.36,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling this topic is heading in a direction I don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:50.37,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.91,0:05:56.00,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Scar is apparently up north.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:05:59.29,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,So are the Elric brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:02.21,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.13,0:06:07.30,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,My old classmates, Lucy and Ian, are also up north.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:08.93,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,They tell me many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:14.06,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, the north and the east will be holding joint exercises in the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:19.69,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we've been defeated countless times by Major Miles and Captain Buccaneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:22.77,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Miles... Buccaneer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:27.57,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,York, Ida, and Sugar, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.03,0:06:35.70,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Havoc, Oscar, Mike, Uni, Nora, Charley...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.70,0:06:38.08,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Uni again, then Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:43.00,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Uni comes again, then next... is Sterling!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.84,0:06:48.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,"Selim Bradley is Homunculus".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.55,0:06:55.72,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's no way that {\i1}can't{\i0\fscx30} {\r} be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:07:02.40,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is about to happen here in Central?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.16,0:07:14.28,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.70,0:07:18.50,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:20.21,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.21,0:07:21.71,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:24.84,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:28.67,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.67,0:07:30.13,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.13,0:07:34.59,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you at least a little surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:37.06,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,If I do get surprised, will you give me something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.06,0:07:40.56,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're always at ease. I like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:42.60,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:44.40,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Slave Number 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.40,0:07:48.40,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't ask for a number. I want your real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.69,0:07:50.82,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a name. I'm a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:52.03,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:58.08,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,People who are stripped of their rights and freedom, and are exchanged as possessions in conveyance?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.08,0:07:59.20,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Conveyance?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:03.25,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,To transfer property and rights and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.67,0:08:07.25,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,You're not very bright, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.25,0:08:08.59,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.59,0:08:13.30,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand how I was born from someone like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:17.22,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who gave me blood, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.89,0:08:23.06,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,They did take a lot of blood from me to use for experiments...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:27.77,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I was born because you gave me blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.73,0:08:31.86,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:35.32,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,"Slave Number 23" just sounds too cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.32,0:08:37.66,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a name, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.66,0:08:39.53,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.53,0:08:43.41,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want a cool name? Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:47.88,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Teo... Teofrastus Bombastus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:47.88,Default-alt,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:54.26,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it can't be too long; else you won't be able to memorize it. You're dumb, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.26,0:08:55.47,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Quit saying that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:57.76,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about Van?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.76,0:09:00.81,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Van Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:02.77,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Van Hohen, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.23,0:09:05.56,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I should be able to remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:07.19,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,You spell it like...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:09.94,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, do you know how to read and write?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:12.78,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need to know to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.78,0:09:14.61,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,The work of a slave, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:19.37,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want freedom and rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.37,0:09:25.25,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Do you plan on ending your life as a slave without gaining basic human rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:31.17,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,That's the same as being in this stuffy flask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:36.38,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to share my knowledge with you, Van Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:43.31,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... What {\i1}are{\i0\fscx30} {\r} you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.22,0:09:45.56,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What should I call you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.06,0:09:51.73,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,The Little One Inside the Flask. So... call me "Homunculus".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.74,0:10:09.21,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,All was created from one, and it eventually returns to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.29,0:10:12.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, one is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.71,0:10:15.38,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,All exists due to one...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:17.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,...and all exists within one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.80,0:10:21.47,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If one does not contain all, then there exists nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:24.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.89,0:10:28.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're now a fine alchemist, Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.94,0:10:32.06,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still not good enough to be on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:35.57,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,My abilities are far beneath yours, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:40.32,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I'm really thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:41.74,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:45.95,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Because you gave me knowledge,\NI'm able to live a good life like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:48.62,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also happy to be in Master's favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:53.63,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,It may be possible that I can marry someone in the future and start my own family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.92,0:10:55.96,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,A family, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.96,0:10:58.21,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are inconvenient creatures, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:11:02.97,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,The species can't live on unless they all create a community and expand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.97,0:11:04.85,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.26,0:11:10.48,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,It may be stupid in your eyes,\Nbut having friends and family...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.94,0:11:14.19,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,...may bring one happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:15.90,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,For us humans, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.90,0:11:17.69,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.69,0:11:20.24,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you consider happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:22.20,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:28.95,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be too greedy, but I guess being able to leave this flask would make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.30,0:11:40.01,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Immortality...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.47,0:11:45.68,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why fools who gained ultimate authority and prosperity begin to wish for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.68,0:11:47.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your tongue!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.01,0:11:48.72,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're talking to the King!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:52.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If you continue to be disrespectful, I'll break the flask!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.73,0:11:56.61,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to destroy the source of the knowledge you don't know about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:11:59.61,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,Cease your prattling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.32,0:12:03.61,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,Can you make me immortal or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:05.99,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Growing impatient as you age, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.99,0:12:09.16,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,How sad, King of Xerxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.91,0:12:16.04,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I'll tell you how to achieve immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:21.92,Default,Old,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the construction?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.92,0:12:23.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're making a waterway for irrigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.80,0:12:27.60,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The King ordered a waterway to extend around the entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:30.06,Default,Old,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing less to be expected from the King of Xerxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:33.64,Default,Old,0000,0000,0000,,He even thinks about commoners like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.64,0:12:34.89,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.15,0:12:43.74,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Kill them all. Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.74,0:12:44.65,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.83,0:12:59.63,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Waste no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.46,0:13:03.34,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and carve a bloody crest into the land!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.22,0:13:11.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The village to the north was raided?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:12.68,Default,Women,0000,0000,0000,,I heard everyone there was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.68,0:13:14.31,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And the same thing happened in the village to the west last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.31,0:13:15.94,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who's behind it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.44,0:13:18.06,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,How terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:19.98,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, how awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.38,0:13:44.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty, the transmutation circle is finally complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:50.22,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,Truly, it has been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:54.77,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,This is all we need to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.06,0:13:57.85,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you'll be able to become immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:17.87,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.71,0:14:20.88,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,The King is going to become immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:28.09,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's what they call the turning point of the century.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:47.19,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,So this is immortality...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:53.74,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:15:00.04,Default,King,0000,0000,0000,,You said that since we're in the center of it, we wouldn't be harmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:06.63,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.46,0:15:08.84,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.84,0:15:10.63,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Homunculus!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.30,0:15:17.43,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,The true center of the transmutation circle is where you're standing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:18.27,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:23.56,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I opened the gate using your blood inside of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.19,0:15:27.32,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,You're a relative that shares my blood, Hohenheim!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:31.99,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, you and I are at the center of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.39,0:16:45.19,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.78,0:16:52.90,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:57.12,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:07.17,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Is anyone here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:10.17,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Willard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:12.09,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Mechthild!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:13.92,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Linemile!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:15.51,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Tony!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:17.34,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Meiyou!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.56,0:17:32.03,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Please... Someone, say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:36.61,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. Everyone has had their souls taken from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:40.07,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:43.04,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You were all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:44.04,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:50.00,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,...How do you like your new body?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.00,0:17:52.46,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,It's... me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:57.34,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I created a body for myself using\Nthe information stored in your blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.01,0:18:03.22,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, I can walk with my own two feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:08.27,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You're... Homunculus?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.90,0:18:10.90,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?! What did you do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:15.90,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,In return for you giving me blood, I gave you a name and shared my knowledge with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.90,0:18:20.16,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,I also gave you an eternal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:22.83,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Eternal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.83,0:18:26.25,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Try focusing all of your consciousness into yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:32.79,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you hear the voices?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.79,0:18:39.63,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,The voices of all the people, who lived in this country, sacrificed for your immortal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:43.89,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Well, half of them went to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.77,0:18:48.89,Default,Homun,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your help, Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:01.99,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hohenheim?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:04.78,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It really {\i1}is{\i0\fscx30} {\r} you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:15.00,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I didn't know you were Ed and Al's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:18.17,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect you to be the master of my sons, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:21.47,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you did a lot for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.47,0:19:23.55,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.68,0:19:25.43,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Izumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:27.60,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Izumi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.31,0:19:30.02,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get your medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.02,0:19:31.39,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Let me take a look at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:34.73,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I know a thing or two about medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.99,0:19:43.57,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, this isn't anything new.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.49,0:19:45.95,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,This is certainly something to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.28,0:19:48.95,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Sig, please get a cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.87,0:19:50.75,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:52.46,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.92,0:19:57.96,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Izumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.63,0:20:02.30,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You saw the truth, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:05.05,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,What did you sacrifice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.18,0:20:08.68,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't try to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:15.94,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,They took a few of my organs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:19.40,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to revive my dead baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:22.95,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.87,0:20:27.45,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.54,0:20:30.91,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:51.14,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.14,0:20:52.39,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.73,0:20:55.35,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Dear. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.69,0:20:57.15,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You were stabbed in the stomach!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.81,0:21:00.48,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But I can breathe more easily now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:02.15,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Show me your wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:05.20,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:07.74,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.08,0:21:15.08,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,The organs that were taken are the proof of your sins, so I can't bring them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:19.17,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,But I rearranged your insides a bit to ease the flow of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.17,0:21:23.55,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Izumi, you can't die just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.63,0:21:26.84,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hohenheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.64,0:21:30.30,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Just... what exactly {\i1}are{\i0\fscx30} {\r} you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.06,0:21:37.98,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a human by the name of Van Hohenheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:41.02,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,A philosopher's stone in human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.49,0:23:16.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The Philosopher's Stone,\Nthe Heavenly Stone, the Great Elixir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.95,0:23:19.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Just like how the philosopher's stone has many names,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.46,0:23:21.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,its form isn't always that of a stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.21,0:23:26.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The one Doctor Marcoh had was almost like a gel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.13,0:23:31.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee's looked like a crystal, and it was about this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.26,0:23:35.76,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Since it possesses so much energy, I pictured something far larger...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.76,0:23:39.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen one bigger than a pebble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.48,0:23:46.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If it's something even larger, that would mean an enormous number of humans was used to create it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:51.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not see one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.99,0:24:03.25,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.17,0:24:07.17,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That is the principle behind alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.17,0:24:10.13,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It is also the principle behind everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.22,0:24:15.80,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:18.85,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 41, The Abyss.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.10,0:24:25.48,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,His softness seeks pain from the boy as an equal exchange.
